API Design
Example Endpoints
Users
GET /users → Get all users
GET /users/:id → Get specific user
POST/users → Create user
PUT /users/:id → Update user
DELETE /users/:id → Delete user

Posts
GET /posts
GET /posts/:id
POST /posts
PUT /posts/:id
DELETE /posts/:id 


Setup Instructions
Implementation Steps
1. Project Setup
Initialized Node.js project
Installed dependencies
Created folder structure

2. Server Setup
Created Express server in server.js
Configured middleware

3. Mock Data
Used mock data instead of database

4. Middleware
Error handling middleware
Async handler
Response formatter

5. Controllers
Created controllers for users and posts
Implemented CRUD logic

6. Routes
Defined routes for each resource

7. Content Negotiation
Implemented response formatting based on MIME types

8. API Documentation
Created docs.html file

Setup code
1. Clone or Create Project
mkdir social-media-api
cd social-media-api

2. Initialize Project
npm init -y

3. Install Dependencies
npm install express morgan cors helmet
npm install nodemon --save-dev

4. Environment Variables
Create .env file:
PORT=3000

5. Run the Server
npm run dev